    "narrative": "The Austin Waves face a challenging slate today, navigating several elite opposing arms that compress our ceiling. **Kyle Tucker** (76.51) and **Jackson Merrill** (70.76) serve as our undisputed anchors; both benefit significantly from favorable platoons against Rea and Gallen, respectively, with **Kyle Tucker** bolstered by wind conditions that push his already elite offensive profile into the high 70s. **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (70.45) also remains an essential play, as his xwOBA profile and a dynamic platoon advantage against the lefty Cantillo keep him firmly in the elite tier despite a moderate matchup. These three represent our best path toward volume production in the R, HR, and RBI categories, which are critical given our emphasis on maintaining efficiency in a tight race.\n\nOur most difficult roster decision today was keeping **Coby Mayo** (47.14) on the bench. While the park factors in his matchup against Crochet provide a 16% lift, his projected efficiency simply could not overcome the extreme negative impact of facing such an elite pitcher. The decision to prioritize **Jacob Wilson** (55.76) and **Josh Jung** (59.81) came down to their superior command of the plate and higher relative scores against their respective left-handed starters. Meanwhile, the bottom of our lineup remains volatile; **Nasim Nunez** (44.77) and **Drake Baldwin** (46.69) are starts we are monitoring closely. While **Drake Baldwin** is batting second, his efficiency is severely throttled by Wheeler\u2019s 2.73 xERA, illustrating the \"avoid\" risk we face when our players run into top-of-the-rotation arms.\n\nWe must remain vigilant regarding the high-end pitching we are facing across the board. The heavy weight of Crochet, Wheeler, and Gallen on today\u2019s schedule significantly depresses our aggregate score, forcing us to bench high-upside players like **Nolan Schanuel** (40.20) and **Brady House** (38.63) to protect our total game caps. **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** remains completely excluded from calculations due to his absence from the confirmed lineup, while our broader roster\u2014including **Luis Robert Jr.**, **Jordan Westburg**, **Jorge Polanco**, **Josh Lowe**, **Marcell Ozuna**, **Dominic Smith**, and **Liam Hicks**\u2014will remain on standby to plug holes should injuries or late-day lineup changes occur. With SB scarcity in mind, we are banking on **Kyle Tucker** and the top-order agility of **Gunnar Henderson** to keep our baserunning metrics afloat despite the stiff opposition.",
